COMPILATION AND EXECUTION
======================================================================================================================================


- A) Coupling the Spring-Mass-Damper (SMD) and compiling SMUQ:
——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————

1. Add the following lines to the bashrc file (vim ~/.bashrc)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

####################################################### SMUQ #####################################################################
alias SMUQ-COMPILE-INSTALL='"$SMUQ_PATH"/SMUQ-"$SMUQ_VERSION"/exec/CompileInstall-SMUQ.sh'

function SMUQ-gfortran-release-application {  
export SMUQ_COMPILER="gfortran"
export SMUQ_COMPILER_VERSION="gnu-7.3.0"
export SMUQ_DISTRIBUTION="release"
export SMUQ_VERSION="3.0"
export SMUQ_PATH="/home/rstkwsk2/workspace/repos/smuq/SMUQ"
export SMUQ_TASK="application"
eval 'source "$SMUQ_PATH"/SMUQ-"$SMUQ_VERSION"/exec/Export-SMUQ.sh'
}
##################################################################################################################################

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

2. Upload the environment variables of external code handlers ( SMD )

3. Update the bashrc file (source ~/.bashrc)

4. Upload the environmental variables and libraries by typing SMUQ-$SMUQ_COMPILER-$SMUQ_DISTRIBUTION-$SMUQ_TASK.

5. Finally, type SMUQ-COMPILE-INSTALL. SMUQ is now installed in the folder $SMUQ_INSTALL_DIR.


- B) TESTING SMUQ:
——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————

1. Create a run directory

2. Copy from ${SMUQ_PATH}/SMUQ-${SMUQ_VERSION}/exec the run_SMUQ.sh script into the run directory

3. Copy ${SMUQ_PATH}/SMUQ-${SMUQ_VERSION}/cases/SMD/bayesian_kcdeterministic to run directory and rename as 'case'

4. Copy ${SMD_PATH}/SMD-${SMD_VERSION}/cases/basickc to run directory and rename as 'extcase'

5. Run the run-SMUQ.sh bashscript inside the run directory
  -- can specify number of concurrent chains as nprocesses=<nbchains>
  -- can perform steps 3 and 4 in step 5 by adding case=<casedir> and extcase=<extcasedir>
  -- order of script arguments does not matter

6. When the simulation is done, postprocess the results by executing from the output folder the appropriate MATLAB script
